\title{Left cosets of normal subgroup are also right cosets}
\author{alex-nelson}
\import{notation}
\date{2025-12-16}
\taxon{corollary}

\p{Let #{G} be a [[gr-000G]], let #{N\normalsubgroup G} be a [[gr-002P]] of #{G}. Then any left coset of #{N} is also a right coset of #{N}. That is to say, we may just speak of "cosets of #{N}" since all left cosets are right cosets of #{N}.}

\proof{\p{Immediately follows from [[gr-003M]].}}